For the fact cp. the inscription on the Parian Marble, 43 [ἑ]τε’θη ὁ τράγος [ἆθλον] ; see Bentley’s Phalaris xi. Horace is no doubt follow- ing the etymology commonly given in antiquity to τραγῳδία, but his object is to link the origin of the satyric drama with that of tragedy. This is done as effectually by the more recent view that it was called the ‘goat song’ from the chorus of goats or satyrs.
